1 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES - FLOOR VERSION
2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
4 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
FOR
5 HOUSE BILL NO. 4106 By: Ford
6
7
8 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to crimes and punishments; amending
21 O.S. 2021, Sections 1704 and 1706, which relate to
10 grand and petit larceny; decreasing threshold amount
for grand larceny offenses; providing felony penalty
11 for third and subsequent petit larceny convictions;
and providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 1704, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 1704. Grand larceny is larceny committed in either of
18 the following cases:
19 1. When the property taken is of a value of One Thousand
20 Dollars ($1,000.00) Nine Hundred Dollars ($900.00) or greater; or
21 2. When such property, although not of a value of One Thousand
22 Dollars ($1,000.00) Nine Hundred Dollars ($900.00) or greater, is
23 taken from the person of another.
24 Larceny in other cases is petit larceny.
HB4106 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 1706, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 1706. A. Petit larceny shall be punishable by a fine
4 of not less than Ten Dollars ($10.00) or more than Five Hundred
5 Dollars ($500.00), or imprisonment in the county jail not to six (6)
6 months, or by both such fine and imprisonment, at the discretion of
7 the court.
8 B. Any person convicted of a third or subsequent offense of
9 petit larceny shall be guilty of a felony, punishable by
10 imprisonment in the custody of the Department of Corrections for a
11 term not exceeding two (2) years, or a fine not exceeding One
12 Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), or by both such fine and imprisonment.
13 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
14
15 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON JUDICIARY AND PUBLIC SAFETY
OVERSIGHT, dated 02/26/2026 - DO PASS, As Amended.
